items.title: Sea cucumber - Wikipedia
items.snippet:
In most sea cucumbers, this is the only substantial part of the skeleton, and it 
forms the point of attachment for muscles that can retract the tentacles into the 
body for safety as for the main muscles of the body wall. Many species possess 
an oesophagus and stomach, but in some the pharynx opens directly into the 
intestine.

items.title: Reproductive system - Wikipedia
items.snippet:
Vertebrate animals all share key elements of their reproductive systems. They all 
have gamete-producing organs or gonads. In females, these gonads are then 
connected by oviducts to an opening to the outside of the body, typically the 
cloaca, but sometimes to a unique pore such as a vagina or intromittent organ.
